mistral.reason: Saiyuki (manga) is the original work by Kazuya Minekura, while Saiyuki Gaiden is a spin-off or side story of the original series that takes place in Heaven, 500 years before the events of the main story. Therefore, Saiyuki and Saiyuki Gaiden are separate titles within the same universe.

gemma2.reason: Context information states "Saiyuki Gaiden" is the name of an OVA for "Saiyuki", a separate manga series.

llama3.1.reason: The title of the manga Saiyuki is actually "Saiyuki" (最遊記), not "Saiyuki Gaiden", which is a different work as mentioned in points 1 and 6.

qwen2.5.reason: Saiyuki Gaiden refers to a separate manga series published between 1999 and 2009, not the title of the main Saiyuki manga. The main Saiyuki manga by Kazuya Minekura does not have 'Saiyuki Gaiden' as its title.
